Point the plugin at your [[Familiar|https://github.com/mblackman/tiddly-familiar]] server. Changes take effect on the next request — no reload needed.

!!! Gateway URL

Base URL of the gateway server (a trailing slash is ignored):

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/GatewayURL" tag="input" default="" placeholder="http://localhost:8787" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! API key

The `GATEWAY_API_KEY` value from the gateway's `.env`, sent as the `X-API-Key` header. Leave empty if the gateway runs without one:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/APIKey" tag="input" type="password" default="" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! Chat note title template

Proposed title for notes created by ''New note'' and the ''new AI chat'' page button. Tokens: `{name}` (random adjective-noun), `{date}` (YYYY-MM-DD), `{time}` (HH:MM):

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/ChatNoteTemplate" tag="input" default="" placeholder="AI Chat: {name}" class="fam-settings-input"/>

---

!! Advanced — retrieval tuning

Optional. Each control overrides a gateway default per request; leave it ''blank'' to keep the server's own setting. Changes take effect on the next request — no reload needed.

!!! Notes per answer

How many top-ranked notes the familiar reads before answering (gateway `RAG_TOP_K`, default 8). More notes = more context, but slower and costlier asks:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/RagTopK" tag="input" type="number" default="" placeholder="server default (8)" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! Follow-up query rewrite

For chat follow-ups, rewrite the question into a standalone search query before retrieving (gateway `RAG_QUERY_REWRITE`). Improves follow-up relevance at the cost of one extra generation call per turn:

<$select tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/QueryRewrite" default="" class="fam-settings-input">
<option value="">Server default</option>
<option value="yes">On</option>
<option value="no">Off</option>
</$select>

!!! Embedding budget per request

Max notes embedded per request (gateway `max_tiddlers`, default 100) — the cache-miss ceiling, not the candidate pool. Raising it warms a large wiki's index in fewer asks, at higher per-ask cost:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/MaxTiddlers" tag="input" type="number" default="" placeholder="server default (100)" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! Search results shown

How many results the sidebar semantic search returns:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/SearchResultCount" tag="input" type="number" default="" placeholder="default (10)" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! Related notes shown

How many related notes the ''Related'' tool suggests per note:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/familiar/RelatedCount" tag="input" type="number" default="" placeholder="default (5)" class="fam-settings-input"/>

!!! Reset

Restore the five tuning knobs above to the gateway's own defaults. This clears your overrides only — the gateway URL, API key, and title-template settings are left untouched:

<$button class="fam-settings-input">
<$action-deletetiddler $filter="[prefix[$:/config/mblackman/familiar/]] -[[$:/config/mblackman/familiar/GatewayURL]] -[[$:/config/mblackman/familiar/APIKey]] -[[$:/config/mblackman/familiar/ChatNoteTemplate]]"/>
Reset retrieval settings to defaults
</$button>

---

!! Sync status

The plugin keeps the gateway's note cache warm in the background so answers can draw on your whole wiki. Check coverage here — if ''awaiting sync'' stays high or ''server holds'' is far below ''notes tracked'', some notes aren't reaching the server yet. Use ''Sync now'' to force a full pass.

<table class="fam-sync-status">
<tr><td>State</td><td><$text text={{{ [{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status}match[ready]then[In sync]] ~[{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status}match[syncing]then[Syncing…]] ~[{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status}match[scanning]then[Scanning wiki…]] ~[{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status}match[degraded]then[Gateway unreachable — asks still work, sync will retry]] ~[Not started] }}}/></td></tr>
<tr><td>Notes tracked (this wiki)</td><td><$text text={{{ [{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status!!total}else[—]] }}}/></td></tr>
<tr><td>Confirmed on server</td><td><$text text={{{ [{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status!!synced}else[—]] }}}/></td></tr>
<tr><td>Awaiting sync</td><td><$text text={{{ [{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status!!unsynced}else[—]] }}}/></td></tr>
<tr><td>Server holds (all cached notes)</td><td><$text text={{{ [{$:/temp/familiar/sync-status!!server}else[—]] }}}/></td></tr>
<tr><td>Last checked</td><td><$view tiddler="$:/temp/familiar/sync-status" field="checked" format="date" template="YYYY-0MM-0DD 0hh:0mm"><span>—</span></$view></td></tr>
</table>

<$reveal state="$:/temp/familiar/sync-status" type="match" text="syncing" tag="span">
<$button class="fam-settings-input" disabled="yes">Syncing…</$button>
</$reveal>
<$reveal state="$:/temp/familiar/sync-status" type="nomatch" text="syncing" tag="span">
<$button class="fam-settings-input">
<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-familiar-sync"/>
Sync now
</$button>
</$reveal>

//"Server holds" counts every distinct note version the gateway has cached (shared across wikis, edited notes linger until the 30-day cache TTL), so it can read a little higher than this wiki's note count.//
